President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Montana due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency protective measures, including direct federal assistance, in all areas impacted by COVID-19 in Montana. Lee K. dePalo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future if requested by the state and warranted by further assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.